title: Chili Cheese Bubble Up
directions: Open the can of biscuits and cut each one into four equal pieces. Place the cut pieces of uncooked biscuit into a mixing bowl and add the melted butter, the parsley flakes and the garlic powder. Toss thoroughly making sure the mixture covers all the biscuit pieces.

Coat an 8-inch-by-8-inch baking tray with cooking spray. Add the two cans of chili beans and the six hot dogs cut into bite size pieces. Layer on the shredded cheddar cheese and top off with the biscuit pieces.
Place the tray in the oven and bake for 375 degrees F for 20-22 minutes.
When cooked the wonderful gooey chili-cheese combination will be topped off by a layer of perfectly browned biscuits.
